abstract: The network equipment maker reported that its quarterly net income grew 7.2 percent amid growing concern that economic weakness could affect technology spending this year.
snippet: The network equipment maker reported that its quarterly net income grew 7.2 percent amid growing concern that economic weakness could affect technology spending this year.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO _  Cisco Systems, the largest network equipment maker, surpassed Wall Street’s sales targets slightly as it announced quarterly earnings on Wednesday, but it forecast a slowdown in orders for the current quarter in the face of tightening corporate budgets.

headline.main: Cisco Profit Up, but Shares Fall on Cautious Outlook
